<br>
Lets say im in a group and someone needs a rez.. I will ask my group if they mind if I rez someone.. why? cause yes its downtime for me AND them.  They have to hold pulls etc..   And when in a group, rarely clerics are FM.. so chances are that after the rez, healing that person and buffing them a little.. you will most likely be OOM and have to med before starting pulls again.  And yes.. I will split with the group the donation I got.<br>
<br>
Exemple, I rezzed a whole group of you guild yesterday in Towers, my group had just came up on 6th floor and we had med to full down on 5th so that we are ready to pull once up there.  So initialy.. we would of went up and started pulls right away.. but I rezzed 5 persons at entrance.  That caused 20 min of downtime.  Rezzed them, healed them and buffed them.  The mage with us even used all her mana on summoning rods so I could rez them all as quickly as I could cause I know how annoying it can be waiting for a rez.  So I was out of mana, mage oom, my groups buff fading.. its a question of getting ready all over again for pulls.  They all donated.  In normal situation, if im doing nothing and have the time and the mana for it, I WILL refuse donations, but when it takes some time out of my playing, grouping and downtime on all my group.. donations are welcome.<br>
<br>
So all this to say that yes.. sometimes the cleric will accept the donations for the &quot;downtime&quot; it causes him/her and the group.<br>
<br>
Also like others said.. most ppl do offer /shout for rezzs and TP's with a donation.. cause they know most of the time they will get the service fast.  The other day my whole group needed a corpse summon... I just did a /who all nec  and asked one if he would be willing to do 4 summon corpses for 500pp and cost of coffins... he said he was on his way... do you think if we would have shouted &quot;Looking for 4 summon corpse at XX zone&quot; we would of had an immediat response?  I doubt it.<br>
<br>
Why offer him 500pp?  Because of his downtime.  Time to get to us, mana spent for 4 cast of summon corpses, time to go back to what he was doing.<br>
<br>
You will never catch me sitting in a zone shouting &quot;rezzing at zone for donations&quot;.. why? Cause if im sitting at zone waiting to rez ppl.. then its not downtime.. and im actualy OFFERING ppl to rez.  <br>
<br>
Often when im running to somewhere and I see a corpse.. I check if that person is online and without notice I cast rez on the corpse and continue my journey.  Then get a tell from that person asking where I am so he can donate.. I tell him its fine and to have a good day... cause he didnt ask, didnt cause me any downtime and maybe made his day.<br>
<br>
So.. I think yes.. most of the time.. donations are for downtimes when the cleric accepts the donation.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cents..<br>
<br>
